{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PGo5LFSx7z8Y2ca7XG5wvq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BGUoqASrz8pzGmAvPjiRkE","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Session retrospective #63","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --json` to get token consumption data.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nCONTEXT: This is the 63rd consecutive no-op session. The sprint is 100% complete (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics all done). The ONLY work done was fixing Ralph's state corruption — it keeps reverting stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` every session. Ralph must be stopped.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session #63, state corruption fix only\n2. **Issues analysis** — Ralph state corruption is the critical ongoing issue\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report, focus on waste from no-op sessions\n4. **What went well** — efficient fix of known issue\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph still running, wasting tokens\n6. **Lessons learned** — need automatic Ralph shutdown when sprint complete\n7. **Action items** — STOP RALPH\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md where date is today (2026-03-28).\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":61725,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe6dc63a-7569-4030-9022-fcaa7e2b86b1","uuid":"9942ec73-be2b-43d7-bb97-4b7cf5e37f33"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"aaa0e2052f8c0847a","tool_use_id":"toolu_01BGUoqASrz8pzGmAvPjiRkE","description":"Session retrospective #63","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --json` to get token consumption data.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nCONTEXT: This is the 63rd consecutive no-op session. The sprint is 100% complete (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics all done). The ONLY work done was fixing Ralph's state corruption — it keeps reverting stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` every session. Ralph must be stopped.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session #63, state corruption fix only\n2. **Issues analysis** — Ralph state corruption is the critical ongoing issue\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report, focus on waste from no-op sessions\n4. **What went well** — efficient fix of known issue\n5. **What went wrong